Trump’s announcement that the U.S. will take ownership of Gaza has sent shockwaves through global politics. In a move that redefines his presidency, Trump, standing beside a visibly stunned Netanyahu, laid out plans that critics are calling imperialism and land theft. The reaction has been fierce, with figures across the spectrum—Glenn Greenwald, Max Blumenthal, and others—condemning the move. How does this fit into Trump’s broader foreign policy, from his tariffs on Mexico to his past comments on Greenland? And what does this mean for Gaza’s displaced population?
title: Gaza Takeover? Trump’s Bold Plan Sparks Global Outrage  – SF532
